        "title": "feat(media): force Telegram image generation as documents",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Telegram users receiving `image_generate` results could get generated images through photo-style delivery, which can recompress media and make generated image artifacts less reliable to save, inspect, or forward as original files.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis change treats Telegram `image_generate` outputs as document/file media where supported. It keeps the existing direct Telegram delivery behavior and also propagates `forceDocument` through source-reply, block-reply, queued tool-media, and outbound delivery payload paths so the normal active generated-media reply path preserves the document-delivery preference too.\n\nThe change is intentionally scoped to delivery metadata. It does not alter image generation providers, media file creation, or non-Telegram channel behavior.\n\nAI-assisted: yes; the final patch was reviewed with focused local tests and type/lint checks.\n\n## User Impact\n\nTelegram users should receive generated image outputs as document/file attachments instead of recompressed photo messages. That makes image-generation artifacts more faithful to the generated file and avoids losing file/document affordances in Telegram.\n\n## Evidence\n\nLocal verification on commit `ffb71a9a42b3c9933215dc2141efd0157f03b2a9`:\n\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 <18 changed files>` passed.\n- Focused tests passed: 357 tests across:\n  - `src/agents/runtime-plan/types.compat.test.ts`\n  - `src/infra/outbound/deliver.test.ts`\n  - `src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.send-validation.test.ts`\n  - `src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts`\n  - `src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.handlers.messages.test.ts`\n  - `src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.handlers.tools.media.test.ts`\n  - `src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.handlers.tools.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --noEmit` passed.\n- `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts` passed.\n- `pnpm check:test-types` passed.\n- Targeted oxlint on the changed TypeScript files passed with 0 warnings / 0 errors.\n\nOperational note: full local `pnpm lint` was started but the small VM killed the extensions shard with SIGKILL after the core shard passed. `pnpm check:changed` attempted Blacksmith Testbox delegation, but this local environment does not have the `blacksmith` executable installed. CI should run those hosted gates on this updated head.\n\nNative Telegram behavior proof is still required by repository policy; requesting a Mantis Telegram Desktop proof run in PR comments.\n",
